Place a #pot{} over medium-high heat.

Stir in the @Jasmine Rice{150%g} and about @water{300%ml} (double for 4p). Bring to
the boil.

Once boiling, lower heat to medium, cover with the #lid{} and cook for
~{12%minutes}.

Remove the pot from the heat and keep covered for another ~{12%minutes} or
until ready to serve (the rice will continue to cook in its own steam).

Once ready, add @salt{1/4%tsp}, @sugar{1%tsp} (double both for 4p) and half the
@Apple Cider Vinegar{1%sachet}. Mix well to combine.

Meanwhile, roughly chop the @Mushrooms{150%g}.

Trim and thinly slice the @Scallion{2}.

Deseed the @Chilli{1} and finely chop.

Place a large pan over medium-high heat with a drizzle of @oil{to taste}.

Fry the mushrooms with the white of the scallion for ~{5-6%minutes}. Stir in the
@Ketjap Manis{1%sachet}. Remove from the pan and cover to keep warm (give the pan
a wipe, you'll be using it later).

Meanwhile, trim and halve the @Cucumber{1} lengthways. Scoop out the seeds. Chop
widthways into small pieces.

In a #bowl{}, mix remaining vinegar, @salt{1/4%tsp} and @sugar{1%tsp} (double
both for 4p).

Add cucumber and set aside. Toss occasionally.

Mix @Aioli{1%sachet} with @Sweet Chilli Sauce{1%sachet}.

Add @Gochujang Paste{1%sachet} to aioli a little at a time, tasting as you
go—it's spicy!

> TIP: If you don't like spice simply leave out the gochujang. It will still
> taste delicious without!

In a bowl, carefully beat one @Egg{1} (double for 4p). Season with @salt{to
taste} and @Pepper{to taste}.

To another bowl, add @Breadcrumbs{1%pack} and season with salt and pepper.

Toss the @Diced Irish Chicken Breast{260%g} first in the egg and then in the
breadcrumbs.

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its
> packaging.

> TIP: Notice a stronger smell from your chicken? Don't worry! This is normal
> due to packaging used to keep it fresh!

Return the pan to high heat with enough oil to completely coat the bottom.

Once the oil is hot, carefully add the crumbed chicken to the pan.

Fry until golden, ~{5-8%minutes}. Turn every 2-3 mins and adjust the heat if
needed.

> IMPORTANT: Chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

> TIP: You want the oil to be hot so the chicken fries properly. Heat for
> 2-3 mins before adding the chicken.

Fluff up the rice with a #fork{} and divide between #bowls{}.

Serve the cucumber, fried mushrooms and crispy chicken on top.

Drizzle over the aioli.

Garnish with a scattering of green scallion and as much chopped chilli as you
like (use less if cooking for kids or if you don't like spice).